
Author: Kris Nova




[ Readme for setting up Kubernetes ]
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Edit the config files and hostnames to your like.
To change the hostname see:
   hostnamectl --help

I suggest doing something like the following:

  NAME          LOCAL IP ADDR
  novix-master  10.0.0.36
  novix-0       10.0.0.37
  novix-1       10.0.0.38
  novix-2       10.0.0.39

You can also add entries into /etc/hosts

Edit the config files and have fun




[ Master ]
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Create a master node (make sure to set a hostname first and update the config!)

  kubeadm init --config=master.yaml

View the token information you will need on the node

  kubeadm token create --print-join-command






[ Node ]
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Join a node to the master (make sure to set a hostname first and update the config!)

  kubeadm join --config=node.yaml






[ Cleaning ]
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Use these commands to reset your cluster at any time and start over

  kubeadm reset
  rm -rf /etc/cni






[ CNI ]
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
In order for your cluster to work you must install a CNI provider so after the master is
up do the following:

   kubectl create -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cilium/cilium/v1.6/install/kubernetes/quick-install.yaml
